title: Test
summary: This grouped bar chart has 4 categories of Country on the x axis representing 3 groups: 1-2 physicians, 3-6 physicians, and 7 or more physicians.
Averaging these 3 groups, the highest category is found for Country South with a mean value of 54.33.
The lowest category is observed at Northeast that has a mean value of 37.33
showing a difference of 37.1% with the maximum value.

In case of South, 1-2 physicians shows more dominance than any other Country with a value 59.0 and it has the lowest value 24.0 in West.  However, 7 or more physicians being the 2nd most important group, has the highest value 75.0 for Country South and the lowest 40.0 in case of Northeast.
